{
  "name": "util_lib.py: prepend _util_ / _terminal_ to private funcs (20)",
  "_notes": [
    "Skipped intentionally — collision risk: 'run' (too generic; would break subprocess.run, mock 'run' attrs, variable names) and 'currentTimestampMs' (heavily used; bare-name rename is risky). Treat these as a separate manual decision.",
    "Skipped already-prefixed: shell_waitForFile, terminal_spawnIfNeeded, shell_runWithTimeout, _terminal_running.",
    "Skipped classes: LockTimeout, FileLock.",
    "Terminal-domain helpers ('_terminal*' without separator + '_launch_terminal_background') routed to '_terminal_*' instead of '_util_*'.",
    "'_readSidecar' is util_lib's local copy (jot_lib has its own, renamed separately by the jot config); util_lib's is dead code but renamed for consistency."
  ],
  "mapping": [
    {"old": "_matches_prefix",                   "new": "_util_matches_prefix"},
    {"old": "_slugify",                          "new": "_util_slugify"},
    {"old": "_resolvePluginRoot",                "new": "_util_resolvePluginRoot"},
    {"old": "_safe_call",                        "new": "_util_safe_call"},
    {"old": "_strip_stdin_text",                 "new": "_util_strip_stdin_text"},
